* Install web.py

** Ubuntu/Debian

> [sudo] apt-get install python-webpy

** Others

<http://webpy.org>

* Install mutagen

** Ubuntu/Debian

> sudo apt-get install python-mutagen

** Others

See <http://www.sacredchao.net/quodlibet/wiki/Development/Mutagen>

* Install pybonjour 

** All

See <http://o2s.csail.mit.edu/o2s-wiki/pybonjour>

> cd spydaap

> mkdir media

Media is the default directory where spydaap looks for media files. It
can be change by editing config.py.

> ln -s ~/music media/

Link in all the directories whose files you'd like to make available.

> ./spydaap

Easy daemonizing will come soon.
